import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of stock prices across all companies?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Company')
    ax.set_ylabel('Stock Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', hue='symbol', data=data)
    plt.title('How has the stock price of each company changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Company')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    mean_prices = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=mean_prices)
    plt.title('What is the average stock price for each company?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Average Stock Price')
    plt.xlabel('Company Symbol')
    
    for index, row in mean_prices.iterrows():
        chart.text(index, row['price'], f'{row["price"]:.2f}', color='black', ha='center')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', hue='symbol', kde=True, bins=30)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices for each company?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Company', loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Stock Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
